# Content Rule — Everything Editable Lives in `src/content/site.json`

This project is owned by a **non-technical client (a doctor)** who edits the
website by changing values in `src/content/site.json` on github.com. Cloudflare
Pages rebuilds and deploys automatically.

**Therefore: never hard-code user-visible text in components.** Always route it
through `src/content/site.json`.

## What this means in practice

When the user (or I) adds, edits, or restructures **anything visible on the
page** — headlines, paragraphs, button labels, list items, eyebrow text,
captions, contact details, leader bios, footer links, the page `<title>` and
meta description, etc. — the copy goes into `src/content/site.json` first, and
the component reads it from there.

This applies to:

- New sections / cards / list items I add
- Tweaks to existing copy (typo fixes, rewording)
- Anything pasted in from the client (a new bio, a new headline, etc.)
- aria-labels and button text that the client might reasonably want to change
- The page title and meta description (synced via `vite.config.js`'s
  `transformIndexHtml` and a runtime `useEffect` in `App.jsx`)

## How to do it correctly

### ✅ Good — copy in JSON, component reads it

```json
// src/content/site.json
"hero": {
  "headline": "Building Global Synergy",
  "ctaPrimary": "Become a Member"
}
```

```jsx
// src/components/Hero.jsx
import site from '../content/site.json';
const hero = site.hero;

<h1>{hero.headline}</h1>
<a href="#membership" className="btn-red">{hero.ctaPrimary}</a>
```

### ❌ Bad — text hard-coded inside JSX

```jsx
<h1>Building Global Synergy</h1>
<a href="#membership" className="btn-red">Become a Member</a>
```

### Lists of cards / items

Items belong in an array with a stable `id` field. Icons stay in code, mapped
by `id`:

```json
"services": {
  "items": [
    { "id": "standards", "title": "Standards & Compliance", "summary": "…" }
  ]
}
```

```jsx
const ICON_BY_ID = { standards: Scale, certification: BadgeCheck };
const services = site.services.items.map((s) => ({
  ...s,
  icon: ICON_BY_ID[s.id] || Scale,
}));
```

The doctor edits titles, summaries, and item lists freely. New items with an
unknown `id` fall back to a default icon — never break the build.

## What stays in code

Do **not** move these into JSON — they are structural or visual, not "content":

- Icons (lucide-react imports), colors, fonts, animations, layout classes
- Geographic data on the maps (country coordinates, SVG paths, continent shapes)
- Accessibility descriptions of decorative SVG visualizations
  (`EarthGlobe.jsx`, `WorldMap.jsx`) that are tied to the visual content
- Component logic, refs, effects

## When in doubt

If you're unsure whether something is "content" or "structure," ask:

> Would the doctor reasonably want to change this word without a developer?

If yes → goes in `site.json`. If no → stays in code.

## After adding new content keys

1. Verify `npm run build` succeeds (no JSON parse errors, no missing references).
2. Consider whether `HOW-TO-EDIT.md` needs a new entry in the orientation table
   for a new section / field.
